[Student "S"]
{WEST expects to bid 2NT at his second turn, but EAST gives a positive 2\H 
response and his thinking changes! First he supports \Hs, setting the 
trump suit.

EAST then bids 3\S, showing first round control. WEST tries 4NT (Blackwood) and 
EAST replies 6\C. This shows a \C void and one Ace, obviously the \SA.

WEST bids 6\H, knowing they must lose the \DA.}

